Recommendations
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Require the Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to submit the required copies of PPE Local Road Network Ledger Cards (Annex D format) of COA Circular No. 2015-008; update the yearly required disclosures as needed; keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network; and prepare a lapsing schedule regularly for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year;
Direct the Municipal General Services Officer to maintain and submit Local Road Inventory and Road Maps; and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Cards for all roads and their components and submit the same to the Audit Team (Annex E format) of COA Circular No. 2015-008; and
Direct the Inventory Committee to submit a Report on the Physical Count of the Local Road Network System (RPCLRN) supported with Local Road Network Maps (Annex C format) of COA Circular No. 2015-008.

Create an inventory committee; prepare a timetable for the conduct of Physical Inventory; direct all Department Heads to coordinate with the Inventory Committee for cohesive planning and augment the workforce in the GSO, especially during the conduct of physical inventory taking;

Instruct the Acting Municipal Accountant and GSO to maintain complete property ledger cards and property cards, respectively, for all PPE owned by the agency; and

Direct the GSO to prepare Acknowledgment Receipt of Equipment (ARE) on all equipment as well as Inventory Custodian Slip (ICS) for small items; to provide the property number of all properties; to prepare the list of properties that needs to be insured, submit the list to GSIS and to apply with the Bureau of Treasury for his fidelity bond.

Direct the Municipal Treasurer to ensure that payments to suppliers are made thru checks;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to attach complete supporting documents at the time of the grant of cash advance; and

Consider the designation of another Special Disbursing Officer (SDO) and the establishment of Petty Cash to address petty expenditures of the LGU.

Coordinate with the previous GSO in locating the turnover documents on the above-mentioned structures;

Require the Municipal Assessor to prioritize the registration and transfer of title of the land to ensure ownership by the Municipal Government;

Require the Municipal Budget Officer to provide budget for titling and other necessary expenses; and

Municipal Accountant to ensure land should be properly recorded in the books of accounts and secure deed of donations or deed of sale as basis in the titling and in the recording.

Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare and submit Journal Entry Vouchers drawn for all non-cash transactions or adjustments to facilitate verification in determining the correctness of the amount recorded in the accounts; 

Submit the original official receipts and billing statements from PhilHealth and Pag-IBIG; 

Maintain the subsidiary ledger and general ledger for all accounts.

Direct the Municipal Accountant to revisit the policy on claims of transportation expenses during travel specifically on the use of a hired car and establish rates responsive to the prevailing circumstances;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to require the boarding pass for air transportation travel; and

Require all officials and employees to accomplish the Itinerary of Travel properly.

Require the GAD Focal Person to prepare and submit Annual GAD Accomplishment Report, including all its supporting documents as prescribed under DILG-NEDA JMC No. 2016-1;

Require the Municipal Accountant to submit supporting documents for GAD expenditures; and

Direct the GAD Focal Person to submit the DILG-approved GAD Plan and Budget distinct from the Annual Budget.

We have recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:

a. 	Coordinate with the previous GSO in locating the turnover documents on the above-mentioned structures;

b. 	Require the Municipal Assessor to prioritize the registration and transfer of title of the land to ensure ownership by the Municipal Government;

c. 	Require the Municipal Budget Officer to provide budget for titling and other necessary expenses; and

d. 	Municipal Accountant to ensure land should be properly recorded in the books of accounts and secure deed of donations or deed of sale as basis in the titling and in the recording.

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:

Augment personnel in the Accounting Office;

Require the Supply Officer/General Service Officer to submit the Report of Supplies and Materials Issued (RSMI) to the accounting division; 

Also, require both the GSO and Accountant to maintain subsidiary ledgers for the inventory accounts; and

Strictly comply with the provision of Section 12 of MNGAS, Volume II and Section 114 of PD 1445.

We have recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:
Require the LDRRM Officer to prepare monthly Report on the Utilization of DRRM Fund, certified correct by the accountant, and submit to the COA on or before the 15th day after the end of each month;
Direct all LGU officials to ensure that reports are correct and accurate;
Require the Acting Municipal Budget Officer to prepare and maintain separate registries for the transactions for Local Disaster Risk Reduction Management Fund (DRRMF); and
Direct the Municipal Treasurer upon authorization from Sanggunian Bayan to open a separate bank account for the DRRMF.

We have recommended to the management for executive action:

a. 	Creation of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board in accordance with the provision of law;

b. 	The plan to be reviewed and updated as required by law to ensure its sustainability, relevance and effectiveness;

c. 	Campaigns should be collaborated with the barangay officials concerned; and

d. 	Continued and stricter implementation of waste segregation, and thorough collection of waste based on set schedules.

